---
import { Link } from "@avaya/neo-react";

import {
  CollapsibleColumns,
  Description,
  ExternalLink,
  ImageWithCaption,
  InfoList,
  InfoListItem,
  PageleteSection,
  PageleteSubSection,
  SectionHeader,
  SubHeader,
} from "components";

import image1 from "../imgs/user-interface-1.svg";
import image2 from "../imgs/user-interface-2.svg";
import image3 from "../imgs/interactions-5.svg";
import image4 from "../imgs/interactions-1.svg";
import image5 from "../imgs/interactions-3.svg";
import image6 from "../imgs/interactions-4.svg";

import { topics } from "../static";
const { id, title } = topics.windows;
---

<PageleteSection>
  <SectionHeader id={id}>{title}</SectionHeader>

  <Description>
    Windows is a desktop operating system created by Microsoft that is used by
    many computer systems. You can find an overview of their best practices on
    the <ExternalLink
      href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/apps/get-started/best-practices"
      inline
    >
      Microsoft Build site
    </ExternalLink>.
  </Description>

  <PageleteSubSection>
    <SubHeader id="win-user-interface">User Interface</SubHeader>

    <Description>
      The visual appearance for Windows applications should utilize a
      combination of native elements and Neo styling.
    </Description>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image1.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing various elements."
        captionTitle="Native Elements"
      >
        Applications built for Windows should use native components wherever
        possible to ensure consistency across platforms, while leveraging
        built-in accessibility. Neo fonts, colors, and icons should be applied
        at the design token level where possible.
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image2.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing icons."
        captionTitle="Icons"
      >
        All non-system icons used by Windows applications are available on the
        icons page.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/icons">View Icon Library</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>
  </PageleteSubSection>

  <PageleteSubSection>
    <SubHeader id="win-interactions">Interactions</SubHeader>

    <Description>
      Interactions such as display, responsiveness, accessibility and touch
      targets should follow web standards, as well as the Neo guidelines found
      throughout the portal.
    </Description>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image3.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing keyboard keys."
        captionTitle="Keyboard Shortcuts"
      >
        Shortcuts created for Windows applications must not conflict with
        existing browser and desktop shortcuts. Refer to the <ExternalLink
          href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/keyboard-shortcuts-in-windows-dcc61a57-8ff0-cffe-9796-cb9706c75eec"
          inline
        >
          Microsoft documentation
        </ExternalLink>
        as well as <ExternalLink
          href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/complete-guide-to-narrator-e4397a0d-ef4f-b386-d8ae-c172f109bdb1"
          inline
        >
          Narrator
        </ExternalLink>, <ExternalLink
          href="https://www.freedomscientific.com/products/software/jaws/"
          inline
        >
          JAWS
        </ExternalLink>
        and <ExternalLink href="https://www.nvaccess.org/" inline>
          NVDA
        </ExternalLink> sites for the complete list.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/accessibility/keyboard-interactions">
              View Keyboard interactions
            </Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image4.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing responsive display sizes."
        captionTitle="Display and Responsive Size"
      >
        Layouts need to be flexible and responsive, with scaling to match
        different screen sizes. Accurate proportions improve the composition and
        hierarchy. This ensures consistency and a common user experience across
        all platforms.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/guidelines/layout-grid">View Layout and Grid</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image5.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing accessibility."
        captionTitle="Accessibility"
      >
        Windows applications must be accessible to all users. Learn more with <ExternalLink
          href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/apps/design/accessibility/accessibility"
          inline
        >
          Microsoft's documentation
        </ExternalLink> and our accessibility guidelines.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/guidelines/accessibility">View Accessibility</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image6.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing touch targets."
        captionTitle="Touch Targets"
      >
        Interactive controls, such as buttons, should have a minimum 40px x 40px
        tappable area making them easy to see and use, and to meet
        <ExternalLink
          href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/apps/design/input/guidelines-for-targeting"
          inline
        >
          Window's specifications
        </ExternalLink>.
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>
  </PageleteSubSection>
</PageleteSection>
